H0.text: The cell is what a molecule must cross the plasma membrane into.

H1.text: Circle is the destination into which a molecule must cross the plasma membrane, as assumed in the question.

H2.text: Shell is the compartment a molecule must cross the plasma membrane into.

H3.text: Atom is what a molecule must cross the plasma membrane into, according to the assumption.

A4.text: The cell membrane, or plasma membrane, is a selectively permeable membrane as an outer boundary of the cell that encloses the cytoplasm.

A5.text: The membrane serves to separate and protect a cell from its surrounding environment and is made mostly from a lipid bilayer of phospholipids.
